text: In addition to that, have no hesitation in complaining to the concerned authorities. You can file an FIR or and eFIR and ensure to take two copies of the FIR, which will contain the FIR number, date and the police station. 3/3

name: MissMalini
text: There's no way to stop things unless you don't raise your voice against it. Don't be afraid to call for help or to complain. Raise your voice and be firm. This would embarrasses him and make him step back immediately. 2/3

name: MissMalini
text: Firstly, there's no shame in admitting that someone misbehaved with you. Have the courage to stop anyone trying to have his way with you. Public transport isn't meant for men alone and you have rights equal as them to use these facilities. 1/3

name: MissMalini
text: When you see someone being harassed, you must intervene to check whether she is fine instead of saying silent and passing by.¬†3/3

name: MissMalini
text:
But even after calling them out, if they continue with their deplorable actions, you must not hesitate to report to the police.¬†
Also, if you witness such incidents happening to other women, you must step in to help. 2/3

name: MissMalini
text: Verbal harassment is just as bad as physical harassment.¬†Women are advised to assertively respond to the harassers calmly but firmly to let them know that their actions or words are wrong and unacceptable. Calling them out in a public place might discourage their actions. 1/3

name: MissMalini
text: When faced with online abuse, your first step should be to approach the administrators of the website/platform/application. If you‚Äôre not able to resolve the issue through them, you can collect proof of the abuse and file a criminal complaint at the local police station. 2/2

name: MissMalini
text: Online abuse is any type of abuse that happens on the internet, whether it‚Äôs over chat, posting on message boards and forums, through social networks, playing online games or using mobile phones. 1/2

name: MissMalini
text: If you feel threatened, call the police to let them know what‚Äôs going on. Or simply drive to your local police precinct, and tell them you believe you‚Äôre being followed. Give an officer the information on the car that‚Äôs following you and let them take it from there. 3/3

name: MissMalini
text: If you‚Äôre in your car, stay on main roads that are well-lit and don‚Äôt go down country roads or secluded streets. If you‚Äôre on foot, stay in public areas where there are lots of people. You don‚Äôt want to go down isolated alleyways where you can be cornered. 2/3

name: MissMalini
text: If you‚Äôve established that someone is following you, whether you‚Äôre walking or driving, don‚Äôt go to your house. You don‚Äôt want to reveal where you live. Don‚Äôt go anywhere that will put you by yourself with your pursuant. 1/3

name: MissMalini
text: The type of questions that are asked in an interview can be revealing of the company culture. Pay close attention to what is asked, what is discussed and how the interviewer conducts themself. 2/2

name: MissMalini
text: It‚Äôs tough to outright correct a hiring manager or to¬†refuse to answer ‚Äî and that‚Äôs where tact comes in. Tactfully answering any interview question is your best weapon in remaining composed, calm and focused on what‚Äôs most important: evaluating if a company is really for you. 1/2
